value.value: 重複腎
a kidney that is split into two separate collecting systems; there may be a duplex ureter or a single ureter; may present unilaterally or bilaterally
ガラクトースの恒常性異常
anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of galactose in the fluids and tissues
ビタミンの恒常性異常

anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of organic substances found in food and are not synthesized by the body and are necessary in trace amounts for normal metabolic function
羊水過多症
abnormally high amniotic fluid volume; may result from maternal diabetes, chromosomal abnormalities or other congenital abnormalities
桿体の電気生理異常（桿体による暗順応の異常）
any functional anomaly of dark adapted vision mediated by the rods
錐体の電気生理異常（錐体による明順応の異常）
any functional anomaly of light adapted vision mediated by the cones
染色体数の異常
chromosome count is other than the expected diploid chromosome number
異数性
chromosome count is not an exact multiple of the haploid number
倍数性
more than two chromosome sets are present
一染色体性
one chromosome missing from an otherwise diploid chromosome set
三染色体性
presence of an extra chromosome in an otherwise diploid chromosome set
染色体切断
chromosome instability in the form of increased frequency of spontaneous breakage with or without rearrangements
自発的染色体切断
chromosome breakage due to inherent instability of chromosomes
染色体切断の誘発
chromosome breakage following treatment with a DNA-damaging agent
膵島炎
a histological change in the islets of Langerhans characterized by edema and the infiltration of small numbers of white blood cells
心室間溝の（形態）異常
any structural anomaly of the indentation dividing the two ventricles, comprised of the sulcus interventricularis anterior and the sulcus interventricularis posterior
歯（の数）の過剰（発現）
presence of a supernumerary, i.e., extra, tooth or teeth
腹印（腹底部に線上あるいはジグザグに白い毛）
the appearance of a stripe or zigzag of white fur on the ventrum
舌下腺の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the small mucin-producing salivary glands in the floor of the mouth beneath the tongue, anterior to the submandibular gland
筋弛緩の異常
altered ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions
筋弛緩（能力）の上昇
greater than the normal ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions or increase in the ability of the muscle to lengthen following contractions
リンパ管拡張症
stretched or widened aperture of the luminal space of one or more of the lymphatic vessels

label.value: abnormal cardiac muscle cell glucose uptake

value.value: 心臓細胞グルコース吸収異常
anomalous ability of the cells of the heart muscle to take in glucose

label.value: abnormal susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: 腎臓再灌流障害に対する感受性異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: a change in the likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia

label.value: increased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: 腎臓再灌流障害に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: an increased likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia

label.value: decreased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: 腎臓再灌流障害に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to kidney reperfusion injury

value.value: a diminished likelihood or extent of damage to the kidney when the blood supply is restored after a period of ischemia
pH制御の異常

anomaly in the function of the buffer systems of the body in combination with the respiratory and renal systems that control the relative acidity or alkalinity of the body, as measured by the concentration of hydrogen ion
動脈解離
a pathologic process, characterized by splitting of the media layer of the aorta, which leads to formation of a dissecting aneurysm
細胞周期チェックポイントの機能異常

anomaly in the amount of time spent at the points in the cell cycle (end of G1 phase, end of G2 phase, and during metaphase) which prevent the cell from progressing to the next phase when conditions are unfavorable
有糸分裂の異常
anomaly in the process of cell division including both division of the nucleus (karyokinesis) and the cytoplasm (cytokinesis)
乳内成分の異常
anomaly in one or more of the constituents of milk including protein, lipid, and/or mineral content or in the appearance of milk
急性前骨髄球性白血病

higher than normal incidence of cancer characterized by rapid onset of abnormal leukocyte proliferation, manifesting as a severe bleeding disorder from coagulation abnormalities, and bone marrow infiltration of abnormal promyelocytes and myelocytes
腎臓の交感神経活性異常
any anomaly in the stimulation transmitted by the sympathetic nerves to the kidneys that is primarily adrenergic and modifies kidney function
腎臓の交感神経活性上昇
elevation in the stimulation transmitted by the sympathetic nerves to the kidneys that is primarily adrenergic and modifies kidney function
腎臓の交感神経活性低下
reduction in the stimulation transmitted by the sympathetic nerves to the kidneys that is primarily adrenergic and modifies kidney function
軟骨結合の異常
anomalous or persistent cartilaginous fusion of two bones
眼周囲間充織の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the mesenchymal cells that give rise to the corneal endothelium, corneal stroma, sclera, iris stroma, ciliary muscle, ciliary stroma, and trabecular meshwork of the eye
心房の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the heart atrium, typically resulting in decreased size
心筋緻密層の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the outer, dense layer of the myocardium uniting the epicardium and myocardium

definition.value: Note that the synonyms "subepicardium layer" and "subepicardial layer" are used in older literature to refer to the myocardium compact layer.

value.value: 心筋緻密層の薄化
reduced thickness of the outer, dense layer of the myocardium
心室乳頭筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of one of the group of myocardial bundles which terminate in the chordae tendineae that attach to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves; each ventricle has an anterior and a posterior papillary muscle; the right ventricle sometimes has a septal papillary muscle
乳頭筋の欠如

absence of one of the group of myocardial bundles which terminate in the chordae tendineae that attach to the cusps of the atrioventricular valves; each ventricle has an anterior and a posterior papillary muscle; the right ventricle sometimes has a septal papillary muscle
乳頭筋の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the papillary muscle, typically resulting in decreased size
右心房の拡張
the luminal space of the right upper chamber of the heart is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid
左心房の拡張
the luminal space of the left upper chamber of the heart is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase in contained fluid

label.value: decreased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy

value.value: 筋萎縮に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy

value.value: less than expected wasting of muscle tissue after experimental manipulation (starvation, neurectomy, immobilization, etc)

label.value: increased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy

value.value: 筋萎縮に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to induced muscular atrophy

value.value: greater than expected wasting of muscle tissue after experimental manipulation (starvation, neurectomy, immobilization, etc)
原始結節の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the regional thickening of cells at the rostral tip of the vertebrate primitive streak through which gastrulating cells migrate anteriorly to form tissues in the future head and neck; this region organizes the formation of the three embryonic layers and establishes the longitudinal axis and the polarity of the embryo
心室柵状織の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the supporting bundles of muscular fibers lining the walls of the ventricles of the heart
背部大動脈の拡張

stretched or widened aperture of the luminal space of one or both of the pair of arterial structures of the embryo that supplies each developing somite via efferent segmental arteries; the dorsal aortae articulate with the umbilical arteries, which return mixed blood to the villi of the chorion for reoxygenation
